title: Key Hamas Plotters of Oct. 7 Elude Israel’s Grip on Gaza
abstract: Israel has battered Gaza in its quest to destroy Hamas, without finding the commanders it has named as its most important targets.

title: Stakes Change, but an Old Fight Over a Chunk of South America Flares Again
abstract: Venezuela’s claim to most of Guyana’s territory has been made against leftists and by leftists. It’s been about colonialism, nationalism, Cold War and oil, and it’s complicating U.S. foreign policy.

title: Gaza Truce Talks Bog Down Over Disputes on Aid Inspections
abstract: In Cairo and at the U.N., negotiators struggled to come up with plans for pausing the fighting, freeing hostages and speeding up help for Gazans.
byline: By Farnaz Fassihi, Patrick Kingsley, Aaron Boxerman and Michael Levenson

title: 2 Teens Convicted of Murder in Fatal Stabbing of Transgender Girl in England
abstract: A jury found that a boy and a girl, both now 16, murdered Brianna Ghey, 16, who was stabbed 28 times at a park near Manchester in February.

title: Israel says it has uncovered tunnels leading to Hamas’s ‘center of power’ in Gaza.
U.S. Defense Chief Says Israeli Shift Would Reduce Fears of a Regional War
abstract: The Biden administration is urging Israel to phase out high-intensity military missions in Gaza to avoid broader conflict with Iran and others.

title: Refusing to Accept Loss of Power, Polish Right Occupies State TV
abstract: The sit-in shut down Poland’s main public news station, a possible harbinger of battles to come as the party voted out of power tries to keep its grip on state institutions.

title: Bahrain detains an opposition figure who criticized the country for joining the U.S. maritime task force.
Israel’s deployment of more troops in Gaza signals unshaken intent, experts say.
Sudan’s Army Faces Scrutiny After Major City Falls to Rival Forces
abstract: The capture by paramilitary forces of Wad Madani, a strategic city in the country’s agricultural region, marks a watershed in the civil war that has upended life in the northeast African nation.

title: Nearly all Gazan households are facing a severe lack of food and water, U.N. and aid groups say.
A Wave of Violence Terrorizes Mexico as Criminals Kill With Impunity
abstract: The latest killings have left dozens of Mexicans dead and few held accountable despite insecurity being the public’s top priority going into next year’s presidential election.
byline: By Natalie Kitroeff and Emiliano Rodríguez Mega

title: What to Know About the Remaining Hostages Taken From Israel
abstract: The top political leader of Hamas is in Egypt to meet with mediators, a sign that the two sides might be inching toward a new agreement.
byline: By Rachel Abrams, Aaron Boxerman and Rawan Sheikh Ahmad

title: In India’s embattled news media, women are fighting to be heard
abstract: Journalists have been targeted for harassment, and some women are only allowed to speak to the press if they have a male chaperone.

title: Airbnb to Pay About $20 Million After Charging Australians in U.S. Dollars
abstract: Airbnb admitted in Australian court that it had made “false or misleading representations,” charging customers in U.S. currency instead of Australian dollars.

title: Security Council Delays Vote on Halt in Fighting to Get More Aid Into Gaza
abstract: The United States requested the delay to allow more time for negotiations, according to diplomats.

title: Austin says less intense Israeli attacks would calm the threat of a wider war.
Fractious Immigration Vote Exposes Cracks in Macron’s Alliance
abstract: Nearly a quarter of lower-house lawmakers in President Emmanuel Macron’s coalition abstained or voted against a proposed overhaul. Government leaders denied a revolt was underway.
byline: By Catherine Porter and Aurelien Breeden

title: Blocked by Polish Truckers, Ukraine Turns to the Black Sea to Boost Trade
abstract: The blockade at the border with Poland has crippled Ukraine’s land trade. But a new Black Sea route is providing an economic lifeline.

title: ‘It was a family home.’ Exiled Gazan learns his relatives were killed in an Israeli strike.
